text:
part three of four:

i’m in my mid 30’s, there’s the usual breakdown of old friendships, i had some difficult things happen within business relationships, i’m divorced, there have been feuds in my family, #metoo , i have arguments with my son, i just realised i’m at war with my tummy and digestion and i’m trying to figure out how to dissolve sexism within the japanese tea culture and not just in japan.... .
a couple of months back i read conflict is not abuse by sarah schulman.  she makes the profoundly helpful distinction between normative conflict and abuse. normative conflict is the unavoidable and necessary result of independent people/countries living/existing together, abuse is when one person/state/species uses their power over another. the problem is the two get confused all the time. sometimes people experiencing normative conflict blow it out of proportion and claim they are being abused. sometimes people/counties perceive danger where it is not and overreact causing abuse/war. she suggests courageous, open communication is how to work through these situations so individual responsibilities can be owned, and violence and abuse avoided. 
the part of the book that was missing for me is what to do when the danger and abuse is real and conversation doesn’t work. .

following this inquiry, where i’ve gotten to thus far is putting love and appreciation into the things/people i want to and want me to, and moving away from what i can’t resolve. me in there niggling for things/people to change does not help or create peace. 
all i can do is work on myself and the relationships that are worthy with the energy and resources i have. .
this does not mean only doing the nice things. i’m doing the work to decolonize my mind, i’m using the privilege that i’ve been born with to rattle the pulpits of the patriarchy, environmental exploitation and racism within myself and my community. .
i do this work with tea.

following this inquiry, where i’ve gotten to thus far is putting love and appreciation into the things/people i want to and want me to, and moving away from what i can’t resolve. me in there niggling for things/people to change does not help or create peace. 
all i can do is work on myself and the relationships that are wohy with the energy and resources i have. .
this does not mean only doing the nice things. i’m doing the work to decolonize my mind, i’m using the privilege that i’ve been born with to rattle the pulpits of the patriarchy, environmental exploitation and racism within myself and my community. .
i do this work with tea.

text:
i need feminism because walking alone at night is a death wish. ❁ 
because in order to be taken seriously i need to be the prettiest girl in the room instead of the most hardworking or smartest. ❁
 because when i go out, it will always be my fault if something happens. ❁ 
because i am in love with my guy friends’ feminine traits and it takes way too long to show them. ❁ 
because 1 in 5 females do not have access to feminine products. ❁ 
because some people think that a tampon is more scary than rape. ❁ 
because birth control has become a luxury. 
because i havent had a role model that looks like me until now. ❁
 because the hashtag #whyididntreport should not be trending. 
because i stand with women. ♀
#metoo #womensmarchdenver

text:
the last few days, i've received a couple of messages asking me to give my thoughts on the gillette commercial.

for those unfamiliar, this commercial is another attack on general masculinity, trying to portray our energy as inherently toxic.

it shows a kid crying to his mom because he got mean text messages from his bullies (gee, all of us boys are so harsh), then makes reference to the #metoo movements (we're all sexual savages too), and even suggests that kids wrestling,

or a man in the street approaching a woman he finds attractive is unacceptable, toxic behavior that's contributing to our poisonous society.

i see what they're doing... they're trying to promote a more "civilized" man,

but this "civilized" man is one who has been castrated,

he has had his power removed,

he's a yes-man cuck who can't make a decision, 
who doesn't have a purpose,

who just serves whatever alpha dog flexes on him.

thing is, 
when you try to promote this non-aggressive civilized man, and frown upon any behaviors that allow us to release our aggressive-energy (like rough-housing, sex, and even ragging on each other), you get more toxic masculinity, because this aggressive-energy ends up being released at inappropriate times.

the more you push down a man's aggressive-energy, the more pressure that builds, 
and it's only a matter of time before it blasts off.

if we give our men their power back, there will be less toxicity in the world, 
as men with their power can explore their dark side healthily,

they can stare their demons in the glaring red eyes,

they can wade in their shadows,

speaking of wading in the shadows,

few months back, i had a young man ask me how he could explore his shadows even more, which made me scratch my head, 
but, i answered him extensively. [link in bio]

text:
is there a #metoo version of the story of samson and delilah? i have been living with this works of art, samson redeemed (1947) by norman rockwell. it was commissioned by cecile b demille for his 1949 movie starring victor mature as samson and heddy lamarr as delilah. as i have talked with people about the work, my interpretation of the story has changed — for the better, i think.
...
the movie tells the version i grew up with: our hero, samson, succumbs to the vile temptress, who is working with the philistines to destroy him against god’s purposes.
...
but, there is another, more nuanced interpretation of events. samson has great success due to a two-way promise with god. the success leads to hubris, and samson breaks his side of the bargain by taking on a lover, delilah, from among his sworn enemies. there is no future for delilah. she is a mistress at a time and place where women were considered property. she has no hope of being accepted among the israelites. and, she is perhaps seen as a conspirator by her own people, the philistines. she is a pawn — not a powerful villain — used by both samson and his enemies.
...
in the end, samson repents; pleading for his strength to come back. he does not blame delilah. in sure sign he is back on good terms with deity, samson’s strength is returned.
...
the benefit of this interpretation is not only that delilah may have been a victim herself — both of samson’s lust and the philistine’s designs — but, that samson, despite his bad behavior, was redeemable.
...
one of the strengths of biblical narratives is their ability to find new depth and application with each generation. but, am i stretching the story too much for our moment? is there a relevant and faithful version of the story that could be told in me too era? 
#normanrockwell #rockwell #samson

text:
don’t call us girls: school changes name to reflect modern times and #metoo movement
#
a high performing grammar school has changed its name to reflect modern times and the #metoo movement. denmark road high school has dropped the 'for girls' part of its title following the arrival of a new headteacher. claire giblin joined in 2018 and decided to take action to bring it up to date. ranked 53 among all state schools in the uk, with 70 per cent of all grades achieved at gcse being 9-7 or a*/a, the school's pupils do exceptionally well. the real schools guide ranked it the best secondary school in gloucestershire for the second year running. headteacher claire giblin said: “in the age of the #metoo movement and more enlightened ideas on gender identity, we felt it is important that our students are not labelled ‘girls’. "they are independent, talented, intelligent young women. read more "they are our future leaders; our next generation of doctors, lawyers and entrepreneurs. "it is an amazing responsibility which rests on their shoulders. denmark road will prepare them to change the world irrespective of their gender." claire giblin with her students at gloucester's high school for girls video loading video unavailable click to play tap to play the video will start…
link: https://metoozoo.com/news/dont-call-us-girls-school-changes-name-to-reflect-modern-times-and-metoo-movement/

text:
someone said to me recently “don’t you find it heartbreaking working in #domesticviolence#shelters?”
my reply is “no....it’s a #womensvillage behind those walls and we meet so many brave #courageous #women and beautiful resilient children that the #gift and the privilege  of walking alongside her far outweigh the personal impact and challenge of processing witnessing  her pain and the injustice of what has happened to her.”
see my bio for the link to my film #mandalamagic that tells the story of how #colouringandconversationcircles make a difference in #dv shelters and #community groups.

text: i am a strong woman because of sooo many other strong women standing behind me, beside me, & paving the way in front of me. women are phenomenal & together we are an army. i march for every little girl to know her place is wherever she wants to be. what a blessing to be able to march with my sister- and all my sisters in celebration of divine feminine energy. i march to empower women, i march to protect women. i march because 1 in 3 is not an acceptable statistic & i march because nobody should also have to use the hashtag #metoo. i march because i believe in the kindness and goodness of humanity, the importance of men & women to lift up all women, to protect, believe, & support women. to all the women in my life- i love you; you are strong, beautiful, capable & your voice may sometimes feel like one drop but it’s part of a powerful tide 🌊#womenswave #empoweredwomenempowerwomen #femalesarestrongashell #whyimarch

text: as we remember mlk this weekend we must remember how civil rights activists of the past sought to love their enemies.  it is challenging for us to be warriors of love and light in the presence of so much hate, but it was done in the past and we must do it again. when i think about this in terms of the me too movement, i think about the challenge of survivors telling their stories while also forgiving their abusers.  how do we forgive those who have not apologized to us? who aren't sorry? who have hate in their heart for us? somehow, we must- so we can have the strength to keep fighting.

text:
today i stand in my truth

as 2019 usher in new beginnings,
new cycles and new paradigm shifts... i have shifted my perspective and have a covenant with my creator to emerge into my true self which is divinity in a physical body... my mission is to assist with the healing of the old paradigms that are no longer serving humanity and must cease to exist. 
my calling is to assist my brothers & sisters that have experienced severe trauma and abuse as children. 
the healing has already been initiated... my book #thedevilsbedroom 
is based on my story and how i discovered that the power of the pen was my therapy.

so much more to come... #letstalkaboutitandheal

text:
yesterday. today. tomorrow. we fight not just for women's rights, but all human rights. none of us are free until all of us are free. ✊✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿 i march for the injustices of patriarchy and colonialism. i march for the missing & murdered indigenous women, girls, and two spirit people and their families, for the safety and acceptance of refugees, the racial discrimination faced by people of colour, for people living in poverty and the homeless. i march for the dismantling of cishetero-normativity, for recognition of my non-binary identity, and for lgbtqia2s+ rights. for the end of infant genital mutilation on intersex infants. i march for those who are young and old, for those with disabilities, chronic and invisible illnesses. i march for sexual assault and domestic violence survivors, and the lives lost to the hands of their partners. i march for the undoing of toxic masculinity (not masculinity in and of itself), for men to express their emotions, and engage with behaviours/interests associated with femininity, to support each other and hold one another accountable. i march for the destigmatization of mental illnesses and maintaining access to healthcare and reproductive rights. i march for the special report on global warming of 1.5ºc launched by the intergovernmental panel on climate change, to protest our over dependence on oil, and the infringement of indigenous rights and those forcibly removed from their land. i march and fight for this and so much more. .
.
.
.
.
.
@womensmarchcalgary @womensmarchcanada

text:
when prey becomes predator

young,
innocent & pure.

blood thirsty,
ravenous wolf…
lurking for the unprotected.

the beautiful butterfly
that is still in the cocoon,
clueless and empty,
not yet violated with hurt and pain.

only the light of love,
divinity dwelling within.

the predator smells the aura of virtue.

sinks his venomous fangs into the angelic flesh,
to purge innocence with death.

where there was once joy and wonder…
evil struck…
now only guilt and shame remain.

a domineering invasion of power
and manipulation,
becomes a life changing humiliation.

because the molester was once
the molested.

left alone and unprotected…
force of perverted power usurped
over the powerless,
no one was there to protest this violation.  victim filled with shame and humiliation…
confused how from perversion emerged
sick pleasure and sexual stimulation.

envious of the power of his manipulator,
vows to never be the victim again…
becomes infected with illusion and sin,
accepts his infestation and slithers to the dirt

to seek victims to infiltrate with his
poison of perversion…
this is now his truth.

wears the masks of father, brother, uncle, homie, lover and friend.

while simultaneously spreading his poison over and over again.

able to do so,
because shame and guilt is holding the
prey captive…

however,
justice speaks and
truth has set the captive free!

truth has exposed the enemy,
light shines on darkness…

the prey…
the predator…
healing steps in and
behold a new day!
@cosmic.empress

text: so, i waited a minute to post my thoughts on the #muterkelly #metoomovement as a #domesticviolencesurvivor it was extremely painful for me to watch the #survivingrkelly documentary... i empathized so much, and could relate to the victims stories. i too, was that young, naive, inexperienced girl who believed and trusted a monster! a young girls 1st boyfriend/experience should be full of sweet & romantic memories. not abuse, manipulation, threats & physical abuse. but these #monsters such as #rkelly & my first boyfriend, prey on young, naive, inexperienced girls. so they can manipulate, mold, brainwash, & abuse physically & mentally. people on the outside looking in wonder, "how can she let it happen? why didn't she tell someone? why didn't she just leave?" the answer: #fear a deep fear for your life & that of your loved ones. so please don't ever judge! unless you've lived it. i'm thankful to god, that i'm alive, and here to tell my story. but so many other girls aren't that lucky. i'm thankful that i never ever again fell prey to any kind of abuse ever from anyone else in my life. it only happened to me with my first relationship, at the age of 17, & never again. i'm blessed to have always been surrounded by unconditional love and support. but so many are not as blessed. but this animal aka r. kelly is not the first, nor unfortunately will he be the last. therefore we need to arm & empower our daughters and sons with the wisdom to always, always respect themselves, their bodies, their minds. and demand that same respect from everyone else. as the mother of 2 young men, i've always instilled in them to #respect #praise #honor all young women, the same way they would expect their mom/sister/daughter to be treated. #itbeginsathome #leadbyexample #loveandprotect #muterkelly #metoo

text:
/ / n e w  b l o g  p o s t  by bryan pue / /
“i believe that men are made to do what is right instead of what is easy. they are made to deny themselves for the sake of others.

the unfortunate thing is if this design is not fed or cultivated, it fades and what is left is a self-preserving, pleasure-seeking type of manhood. we’ve all seen and experienced that, haven’t we? 
but the good news is that there is always hope for a new way of living. the transformation in my own life in this matter is evidence of what is possible.

it is only when we call men to the responsibility of real manhood that we will begin to see a positive change in the general atmosphere of our culture. we have to settle it in our minds that male strength does not have to be a weakness, and that male weakness is never a strength.”
—————————————————

text:
昨日は、バレンタインdeけんぽうカフェ☕️ 土曜日に開くのは今回が初めて。
初参加の方が２人来てくれて、新しい話も聞けて楽しい時間でした💓 ★昨日のテーマは２１条★ 『おたくにとって表現の自由はすっごく大事！
自民党改憲草案だと表現の自由が無くなるかもしれない、コミケ開けないかもしれないと思って不安だし、自民党の改憲は絶対ヤダ！
おたくには死活問題なんです』
と熱く語ってくれた初参加の自称おたくサン✨✨ 右から左までいろいろいる『おたく』ですが、この話題だけはみんな共通するんだそうです。

フィフクロのメンバーも、
『こういう けんぽうカフェを、改憲草案にある『公益及び公の秩序を害する活動』だって行政や政府の都合で判断されちゃったりしないのかな。
そうなるともうこういう事も出来なくなっちゃうね』
『きっと制限されるよね。やっぱ自民党の改憲ムリ！』 と話は盛り上がり、憲法ビンゴやったりと、あっという間に２時間過ぎました笑

次は来週、２５日（金）です💝

text:
very proud to have taken this photo for @stevierae_music’s song ‘uneasy,’ released today, an absolutely gorgeous and empowering anthem for the #metoo movement. listen at the link in my @redharephoto bio -
—
sometimes i feel like i’m not doing enough, that i don’t know how to combat the continually exposed xenophobia, misogyny, racism, sexism and overall hatred for the “other.” then i realize that i’m lucky enough to be able to use my skill set as an artist to create work that matters, is relevant and might make some sort of difference. i’m lucky to have the opportunity to collaborate with so many empowered badasses who trust me with the imagery for their messages. art matters. let’s keep making it, and putting strong works of resistance out into the world, because it’s a necessary part of any revolution.
——
thanks for writing this song, stevie rae. and thanks for trusting me with the imagery... and @nissileebeauty with your hair and makeup, @rachpearl with styling and @rachel_garis with assisting and some movement direction. and thank you to all the women who marched today 💪🏾 🙌🏽✊🏻 ✌🏼we got this. #femalepower #teamofwomen #nashvillemusicphotographer #metoomovement #womentothefront #uneasy #newmusicnashville

——

we are heartbroken to hear of the first woman to be murdered by a man in 2019. 
say her name: aiia maasarwe. 
she was a young student in melbourne. she was walking home from catching the tram after a comedy show. she was on the phone to a family member. she should have been safe. 
how does this keep happening?
we know the answer to that. 
it keeps happening because male violence and male abuse is endemic in australian society due to gender inequality supported by social and cultural norms, the impossibility of facing criminal charges for violence and abuse until acts have become deplorable and the damage is already done, the resulting impotency and inappropriateness of police intervention, and the complete lack of help and support for victim-survivors. 
so the real question is, how much longer will we pretend not to know the answer?
statistics show that every week politicians take to delay acting on this issue out of fear of losing votes, another woman will die.
we are heartbroken to begin our 2019 tally:
🖤

text: (cont..) australia gave women the right to vote and seek election in 1902, but which women? there were certainly no indigenous women among them. feminism in australia has been unable to represent intersectional and indigenous rights because we as white women do not have a lived experience of colonisation as oppressor, and have never experienced the level of femicide, forced sterilisation, sexual violence and abuse, our cultures, land and language dispossessed, or our children taken, as indigenous australian women have. the frameworks are very different. aus indigenous feminism sees decolonisation as integral - which pits them in many cases against white women running institutional feminist organisations because we don’t understand enough about our history and what a decolonised aus might look like. then there is the issue of tokenism - bringing woc on board but then not being interested in how their opinions might alter ‘what the focus of this group is.’ not allowing them to be leaders in their own right. considering their views too ‘radical’ and threatening to the mainstream. these are real concerns - if change needs to happen, it happens slowly in most cases, and political savvy is needed. but by pandering to the status quo in ‘order to change it’, do we just protect it? and what of the women on the ground, working for free - white women - perhaps not so well off as people think, having nervous breakdowns because they’re dealing with rape and abuse stories every day, expected to ‘fix it,’ then being attacked for being too corporate, too white, too much part of the problem? where is the empathy and support for them as leaders dealing with complex problems (without pay!!!)? these are questions i’m still unpacking and i always appreciate your opinions; how and in what ways am i part of the problem and solution. let’s talk.  #womenswave #womensmarch2019 artwork by @aluna.ink #isabellamanfredi #feminism #australianfeminism #indigenousfeminism #australianindigenousfeminism #womanism #humanrights #landrights #femicide #indigenousaustralia #metoo #menomore #nowaustralia

text:
when prey becomes predator

young,
innocent & pure.

blood thirsty,
ravenous wolf…
lurking for the unprotected.

the beautiful butterfly
that is still in the cocoon,
clueless and empty,
not yet violated with hurt and pain.

only the light of love,
divinity dwelling within.

the predator smells the aura of virtue.

sinks his venomous fangs into the angelic flesh,
to purge innocence with death.

where there was once joy and wonder…

evil struck…
now only guilt and shame remain.

a domineering invasion of power
and manipulation,
becomes a life changing humiliation.

because the molester was once
the molested.

left alone and unprotected…
force of perverted power usurped
over the powerless,
no one was there to protest this violation.

victim filled with shame and humiliation…
confused how from perversion emerged
sick pleasure and sexual stimulation.

envious of the power of his manipulator,
vows to never be the victim again…
becomes infected with illusion and sin,
accepts his infestation and slithers to the dirt to seek victims to infiltrate with his
poison of perversion…
this is now his truth.

wears the masks of father, brother, uncle, homie, lover and friend.
while simultaneously spreading his poison over and over again.

able to do so,
because shame and guilt is holding the
prey captive…

however,
justice speaks and
truth has set the captive free!

truth has exposed the enemy,
light shines on darkness…

the prey…
the predator…
healing steps in and
behold a new day!

text:
“in today’s society we are faced with many social norms and because of these, arbitrary ideals, men are in constant competition. whether it be a competition with others or themselves, men can only be sedated when they accept or know that they are the very best. this means men will do the most outrageous things to prove that they are the strongest, most intelligent, best looking, or any other quintessential desire. as a young ignorant male i did not understand how these roles played in our society until much later in my life. in the past when i had learned what these roles truly meant, i had endured countless situations where i would be in a competition with myself, trying to become my very best. after years of not accomplishing my goals of being my best self i have came to understand and accept that these ideals are what destroy peoples’ self-perception. in many cases we have already accomplished our greatest desire but due to “our” human nature it will never be enough. what i’m trying to say is, accept yourself for who you are because being like everyone else is boarding or lower your standards for others because nobody's going to be perfect and your “benevolent” desire of others’ attributes are what damages and destroys what really matters.”
•
•
@itssam.lem •

text:
“feminism is the radical notion that women are people.” 🙏🏼 i was moved several times today, honestly overcome with emotion. i need to do things in my life that awaken these senses more often. ::::::::::::: i was so impressed with the amount of young people out there. i was also impressed by the amount of men. there are so many great men who walk along side us every day. 🙌🏼 i am grateful for these men. 
human rights are a huge issue. if you don’t see that in today’s world you need to open your eyes.  the needle has moved, yes, but not without sacrifice and not without a unified voice. we aren’t the first to march and we won’t be the last. this weekend commemorates the worlds greatest civil rights leader- where would we be if it weren’t for his voice? 
if you are reading this and you have never been personally effected by inequality, i am so happy for you, but you are the minority.  just because you do not experience inequality in your own life- does not mean it does not exist.  there is work to be done and we are the generation to do it. 
#metoo #timesup #everyoneshouldbeafeminist #humanrightscampaign  #womensmarchla #wmla

text:
artreach grantee, the f-you: forgiveness project (lead by the incredible tara muldoon) is a social initiative that focuses on the question “what would it look like if you forgave either yourself or another today?”, offering workshops and hosting events featuring speakers and stories from those who have crossed the line from victim to survivor, this project teaches us that finding forgiveness in the process.

on february 5th, f-you is hosting an event at 401 richmond st. w on exploring forgiveness, focused on the healing of survivors of sexual trauma. 
learn more on their instagram page: @projectfword

text:
cuando fui #mamá pensaba en ser mucho más fresca con mis hijos, a diferencia de mis padres, quienes fueron demasiado estrictos. sin embargo, el entender cómo funciona el mundo, en especial el tema del #abuso, me abrió los ojos, y aunque pienso ser más flexible en varios temas, en este, el de dejar que vayan a dormir donde el primo, tío, mejor amigo, etc, hemos decidido con mario (mi esposo), no ceder. acá les dejo algunos de los motivos por los que tomamos esta decisión, a propósito de todo lo que escuchamos a diario lamentablemente frente al abuso. .
el 90% de perpetradores son hombres, y la mayoría se encuentran entre los 29 y 41 años de edad. un abrumador 50% de los mismos son personas conocidas de la familia, siendo amigos cercanos o familiares. .
la edad promedio de abuso es entre los 8 y 12 años, y se conocen menos casos de niños menores de 6 años ya que ellos normalmente no reportan el abuso. .
si bien hay una creencia de que este tipo de abuso sucede más en estratos sociales inferiores, esto no es cierto, el abuso sexual es independiente del nivel social. .
no les escribo para alarmar, pero les comparto lo que dicen las estadísticas al respecto, tenemos la responsabilidad de estar muy atentos.
.
dependiendo de la edad de nuestros hijos, también debemos tocar de forma sencilla el tema de su sexualidad, de su cuerpo y de cómo cuidarlo y protegerlo. no es necesario entrar en detalles, pero sí de irles comunicando desde muy temprana edad que su cuerpo es solo suyo y que nadie puede tocarlos, además de fomentar una buena comunicación con ellos desde pequeños. .
aunque lo sucedido con martha y con tantas otras mujeres y hombres es una aberración total, sostenida por un sistema machista patriarcal, nosotros como padres tenemos que no solo educar a nuestros hijos para que sean buenas personas y seres humanos con valores, sino también, hacer lo que esté en nuestro alcance para prevenir.
.
.
.
#2019 #nomasabuso #niños #nomasfemicidios #nomemates #metoo #niunamenos #niunomenos #hijos #cuidado #crianza #bastademachismo #nomasviolencia

text:
예대넷 활동을 하며 예술대학생들과 이야기하면 늘 빠짐 없는 주제가 예술대학 내의 교수 - 학생 위계 권력에 관한 문제인데요. 이번에 <추적> 60분에서 관련 내용에 대한 보도기획을 준비하고 있다고 합니다. 이에 대해서 공유해드립니다. <추적60분>에서는 예술대 교수로부터 부당한 처우나 갑질을 당한 학생 및 관계자의 연락을 기다립니다. 또한 그로인해 학업을 접은 분들의 제보도 기다립니다.

인터뷰를 하게 될 경우, 인터뷰 대상자의 보호를 위해 음성변조, 대역 등의 방법이 사용될 수 있습니다. (인터뷰가 결정되면 자세한 방법을 논의드리겠습니다)
.
인터뷰에 참여하고 싶은 분들은 아래 번호나 이메일로 연락주시길 바랍니다
.
전화제보:: 010-4596-6288 (추적 60분 - 문자 주시면 전화드리겠습니다)
메일제보:: 60m@kbs.co.kr(추적 60분) / situationyka@gmail.com(예대넷)
.

text:
flowing 🌸🌿 i’ve never felt strong or powerful as a woman but what if i could embody both of those attributes? what if i could step into my full potential as a beautiful feminine being with strength, softness and grace? sometimes as i heal and discover the deepest parts of myself i get a small glimpse of that potential. it’s there, often just out of sight. and it’s the mind that holds me back. it tells me i’m small, insignificant and weak. 
im trying to peel back the layers on this journey to find the true self. she’s there, it’s just a matter of uncovering her. -
-

text:
if everything comes down to debate and winning, let’s look at it like this:
you can’t tell me i’ve lost at basketball because you were playing soccer.

so, meditate on those statements long and hard before you think your rebuttals are solid and your viewpoint is correct. 
please do not think that as a straight white man that i have not been affected by something similar. 
even if you haven’t, others have. 
the sooner you accept it, the sooner you can help us solve for it and stop it.

text:
naomi alderman: voima.
sain gummeruksen joulukalenterista (kiitos!) ennakkokappaleena tämän brittiläisen naomi aldermanin romaanin voima. romaani on lähitulevaisuuteen sijoittuva dystopia, jossa nuorilla tytöillä on voima antaa kämmenistään salamaniskun tai sähköiskun tapaisia iskuja miehille, niin hyvässä (seksi) kuin pahassa (taistelu). nämä iskut voivat jopa tappaa.
miehet ympäri maailman huomaavat, että valta on karannut heidän käsistään.tyttöjen päivä on koittanut ja maailma on asettunut  täysin uuteen asentoon. millaiseen?
romaani on kirjoitettu vuonna 2016, joten se kirjoitettiin jo ennen #metoo -aikaa ja on nyt ajankohtaisemoi kuin koskaan.  romaanin tapahtumat kiihtyvät, vyöryvät, kiitävät eteenpäin. 
tätä kirjaa lukiessa olin oman mukavuusalueeni ulkopuolella ja reilusti. lisäksi toivuin sairaalassa isosta leikkauksesta kunnon lääkehuuruissa.. kirjasta jäi pitkäksi aikaa hyvin voimakkaita mielikuvia. sekä suuri kysymys siitä, mikä saa naisen väkivaltaiseksi?
#naomialderman #voima #tyttöjenpäivä #gummerus #dystopia #5/2019 #lukeminenkannattaaaina #lukemallaviisastuu #kirjahylly #bookshelf #kirjagram #bookstagram

text:
yes we sell skincare, but behind the team are real, hardworking, kind, loving women. as women, we are the creators of life 
on this earth. we are moms, aunts, sisters, daughters. we deserve better. equal pay, for equal work. same funding opportunities for female entrepreneurs as males. let's keep smashing those ceilings ladies.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
more women in leadership roles in the private sector, as well as the public. so we can start shaping policies that affect us; our health. our jobs. our lives and our families'. the decisions that affect us should be decided by us, and us alone. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
we have a right to our bodies. we should have the right to say no, and be heard loud and clear. we should feel we can walk on the streets safely and be free from harm. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
being a feminist, womanist does not make one a man-hating-bitch. that's not what being a feminist is. we love our men. if you believe each and every person has equal rights - you are a feminist. if you are proud to be a woman, you are a feminist. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
when analyzing the last 6 months, it’s evident that i’m learning more from clem than she is from me.
.
it’s a humbling experience to evaluate the world through the female perspective.
.
although i’ve considered myself a feminist for sometime, becoming a father has upped the ante.
.
i’m truly proud to be the father of a girl and a woman of tomorrow.
.
raised in a predominantly male household with 3 older brothers, it wasn’t until university that i started to self-evaluate and re-evaluate my thoughts on gender.
.
the fact of the matter is i was ignorant to the whole thing.
.
i had to truly learn and grow in understanding the barriers women face.
.
more importantly, to continuously challenge myself and expand my perspectives to promote gender equality.
.
i’m thankful to be living at this time of female empowerment and be able to see and hear amazing female leaders shine the light on the gaps women face in the workplace.
.
follow the @clemaroo instagram account as i proudly share my stories of raising a #feminist.
.
#feminism #love #equality #womenpower #girlpower #selflove #feminista #metoo  #womenempowerment #malefeminist #womensmarch #mensupportingwomen.
.
📝 #editedbyafeminist (@toxic_moosh)

text: today is #womensmarch2019.  i could not be at the women's march this year.  i really wish that i could have been there with my sisters, but i'm taking a different path in 2019, and could not be happier about my choice.  after years of not fully understanding why i felt the way i did, i finally realized i needed to create big changes, take a leap of faith on myself, and explore.  i learned, probably later in life than a lot of people, that a woman can be her own hero, and walk her own hero's tale.  #metoo #timesup and #thewomensmovement played no small part in my confidence and encouragement to make my decision.  i knew i could not be the only person to want this life.  taking a step in to the unknown,  following my own truth to the potential dismay of others is the best way i can honor the women's movement.  i would like to find out if it is possible to create changes and still feel joy and connectedness.  it means that it reached me, and gave me the community that helped me embark on my journey.  this is me walking in to the promise of my own hero's tale.  i would even go so far as to call it magical.❤️

text: the conversation must happen! we have to protect our children and black queens!! the @concertcrewpodcast presents episode 112: surviving r. kelly... the concert crew has a deep conversation about the aftermath of lifetimes’ surviving r. kelly docuseries. hear the fellas give their reactions to the docuseries, discuss the pedophilia problem in the entertainment industry, discuss valuing black women, the level of responsibility of r. kelly’s enablers, separating music from the person and much more. also, the concert crew review new music from mick jenkins, kid ink, young scooter, latoiya williams, fat trel and ice cube. link in bio to episode 112: surviving r. kelly... #concertcrew #podcast #concertcrewpodcast #survivingrkelly #rkelly #metoo #muterkelly #lifetime #piedpiper #abuse #protectourchildren #blackqueens #podcastlife #mickjenkins #kidink #youngscooter #latoiyawilliams #fattrel #icecube

text:
a typical everyday call between my son max and i as he goes from work to the gym❤️
me: hi boo! how was your day?
max: you know mom, same old, same old.
me: are you headed to the gym?
max: 35, 35!, 35! the speed limit is 35! yeah, i'm headed there now. what are you fucking stupid?  you're doing what? 20-25 in a 35 mph zone!
me: are you training someone tonight?
max: yeah, then i have to work out myself. holy shit! this idiot is parked in the middle of the fucking road! really? this is where you decide to park your car you stupid motherfucker! 
me: well, make sure you eat something, okay?
max: oh my god! you should see the front end of this car! it's completely bashed in! 
me: is it the car that was parked in the road? 
max: yes! i guess they couldn't pull over into a neighborhood like normal people! no, they just sit in the middle of the road and everybody driving has to slow down to look! 
me: well, i love you baby and be safe.
max: i'm surrounded by idiots. love you too mom ❤️

text:
“what was she wearing?” “if she wasn’t drunk, it wouldn’t have happened.” “she was leading him on.” “she’s lying to get attention.” “she’s ruining his life.” “why didn’t she report sooner?” “why didn’t she just leave?” .
.
somehow its always a woman’s fault for the abuse she receives from a man. today i marched for every single woman who has experienced violence or unwanted advances from a man….we’ve probably all received some sort of unwanted advances from men on multiple occasions, myself included. we all probably know at least one woman who’s been sexually assaulted or has experienced domestic violence. .
.
i hear you. i believe you. i stand with you and i will stand up for you. please swipe through the photos in this post to read some us sexual assault and domestic violence statistics.
.
.
i’m told i have to be very aware of my surroundings when i’m out somewhere alone. i have pepper spray on my keychain just in case. i’m told not to go hiking alone because its too dangerous. i’m told to never leave a drink unattended. i’m told to stay with my group and don’t go off alone. ever since we were little girls, we’ve been told what to do and not to do to avoid being attacked whenever we leave the house. when do we start holding men accountable? when will men care about the safety of women just because they care and not because they have a wife, a daughter, a sister? when will men believe us? when will men stand up for us? for all of us, not just white cis women. this may be a little off topic but as a woman, its laughable to me when men use their fake outrage to pretend like they care about the safety of women when they try to condemn immigrants and paint them as violent rapists. the statistics are loud and clear. american men are not immune to violence. please do not let an old white guy who is scared of brown people trick you into thinking that immigrants are coming here to hurt you. men, if your first reaction is to get defensive when women speak up, you’re not listening.

text:
okay friends, i had to put my pride aside and make a gofundme because i need a lot of help and positive support. a hand full of you know what happened to me back in november. long story short i basically got sexually assaulted where i used to work which led me to attempt suicide. i have been in and out of psychiatric hospitals which led me to be broke and not have any money or a job for that matter. what makes the situation worse is that i will not have a place to live at the end of january. therefore that is why i made a gofundme because i am in a housing and financial crises. there is more to it but that is the short version. you can read more of what happened once you click the gofundme link. if you can't donate i understand but please share it. the more shares the better.

gahhh!!! my anxiety is through the roof. as i am typing this and sharing such a huge and sensitive thing in my personal life with all of you makes me worried and afraid of criticism and judgment. fear is written all over this post and i am sorry. i promise i am not seeking attention or trying to be selfish and make it seem like i'm bumming off of your guys' hard earned money. please forgive me if any of this is triggering for any of you. again i'm sorry and i promise my intention for this fundraiser is because i'm in need of help. thank you for everything.  #metoo https://www.gofundme.com/traumatic-event-leaving-me-financially-distraught

text:
i raise up my voice -not so i can shout, but so that those without a voice may be heard... we cannot succeed while half of us are held back.
honestly walking with everyone today was so inspiring and meaningful. i am so grateful for all of the people who came out in what felt like-30° weather and persevered. it was an extremely emotional day hearing stories of others struggles and successes as well as remembering and reflecting some of my own that i’ve endured. 
#womensmarch #womensmarchottawa #ottawa #equality #metoo

name: Dani Alexander
pre_proc_tweet:
veganism is feminism🚺 
animals have vaginas
just like us

massive thanks to  and  for the delicious donations that really took our outreach to the next level. we talked to many people about female animals whose reproductive abilities are exploited for food.
🦃🐓🐖🐄🐑🐂
chickens ovulate, cows lactate and all female animals make babies for humans to eat their flesh. 
we showed photos of how cows are forcibly inseminated by a man shoving his arm shoulder-deep into them and many people were shocked. we helped people make the connection between feminism and animal rights. we let them know that a diet of animal products is a diet that oppresses females and challenged people to make the transition to a vegan diet staing today. i directly asked people to not leave the women’s march and go eat a meal that causes suffering for other females.
🧀🥛🍩
our table was stocked with lots of different vegan cheeses, a dozen different plant milks, muffins, candy, bracelets, stickers and leaflets. many people were curious to try vegan cheese and not one person said they didn’t like the foods we were sampling. some of our best feedback was from the i, calf viual reality headsets from  that show the dairy industry from a calf’s perspective. every person that watched was very moved and said that would be making changes in their diets. 
this group accomplishment was hard work! i could not be more proud of this team🌱

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text: after the #metoo movement, the amount of reported sexual assaults dramatically increased, but not much had been done with the cases. according to cbc news, “a 2017 globe and mail series found that police in canada determine sexual assault cases to be baseless at a rate higher then for other types of crime, raising questions about the conduct of investigations and the distortion of statistics related to sexual assaults.” a study involved interviewing 33,000 people over the age of 15, showed that 8% self reported sexual abuse as a child (under 15). 24 million canadians have been a victim of sexual abuse as a child. another study showed that 10% of canada’s population had experienced sexual abuse before the age of 16.

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, goverce, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text:
обвинение жертвы - вера в справедливый мир? 
ни для кого не секрет, что в нашей культуре, если речь идёт о преступлении, фокус внимания смещён с преступника на жертву. это жертва должна быть внимательной, это жертва должна соблюдать правила, это жертва виновата, если с ней случилось что-то плохое. особенно активно жертву полоскают, если произошло изнасилование. в нашей культуре насильник - этакое стихийное бедствие. дикий зверь, которого надо опасаться. учитывая то, что насильник - дееспособный человек, это особенно странно. 
среднестатистический обыватель считает, что это правильно, адекватные люди разбираются, почему так. почему мы обвиняем жертву? 
обычно этот "феномен" объясняют верой в справедливый мир. люди думают, что плохие вещи случаются с плохими людьми. или с теми, кто заслужил. не выполняешь правила, не ведёшь себя как надо - получи! а мы хорошие, с нами ничего такого не произойдёт. мы не ходим по ночам, мы не пьём, не надеваем короткие юбки, не разговариваем с незнакомцами, не навещаем шумных приятелей. с нами всё будет хорошо. 
знаете, чем больше я читаю новостей, чем больше думаю-передумываю все эти ситуации, чем больше просматриваю комментариев, тем больше убеждаюсь в том, что вера в справедливый мир - ерунда полная. 
то есть не так. вера в справедливость имеет место быть. кто-то действительно так думает. я хорошая, я правильная, вот я не общаюсь с плохими, со мной ничего и не случается. меня уважают, я не позволяю себя бить и насиловать. я себя так поставила! я выбрала круг общения! я молодец! 
обычно такое пишут женщины. некоторые мужчины тоже пишут. а как быть с остальными? те, которые орут по всему углам "заслужила", "одной гулящей стало меньше", "молодец, наказал"? почему-то их вопли тоже объясняют верой в справедливость, вот, дескать, есть плохие женщины, их надо наказывать. наказали? хорошо. 
вот! вот оно! оно только на первый взгляд - про справедливость. нет. здесь нет никакой справедливости. здесь только ненависть и ничего кроме ненависти. обвинение жертвы нужно для того, чтобы она сидела тихо и не жаловалась.
#насилие #небоюсьсказать #metoo #обвинениежертвы

i grew up being taught only women can be raped and only men can be abusers. ⁣
i grew up being taught to see women as competitors for men.⁣
i grew up with my keys between my fingers thinking it will keep me safe.⁣
⁣
⁣
i march so tomorrow women dont have to. femmism is about equality of the sexes.  female rights are human rights. ⁣
i march for female, male, trans, non-binary equality. because your gender should not dictate your rights and opportunities.⁣

text:
for the past week thoughts, and feelings have been igniting a fire of words burning to be expressed. content warning as i attempt to shine some light into the dark: discussion of violence against women and sexual assault.

last week i watched the 1st half of the surviving r kelly docuseries. why? i couldn't not. although i knew it would bring up anger and sadness and so many other emotions, these women have stories that need to be told and heard and felt, and that anger needs to translate into actions. to me, the most shocking part of it all was the fact this has been going on, these stories have existed for decades and basically been ignored. r kelly's use of power, manipulation and emotional abuse is sadly all too familiar, my heart ached for the young girls and women he preyed upon. but overwhelmingly i was angry that this has been allowed to go on and on and on for so long. people knew, and chose to do nothing.

on friday night i read about the horrific murder of aiia masarwe. it stopped me in my tracks. i'll be honest, i frequently walk around by myself late and night, and whilst i'm sometimes hyper aware, generally i feel safe. maybe this is because i know, statistically, the majority of violence against women occurs behind closed doors, perpetrated by people known to the victim. perhaps it's because i've lived through these experiences and reclaimed my life refusing to live in fear... what hit home was the fact that as women, we are never completely safe anywhere. it doesn't matter how careful you are, you can follow every safety tip known, but it doesn't guarantee you anything. aiia masarwe was attacked whilst on the phone to her sister, walking along a main road half a kilometre from her home. violence a ainst women occurs wherever someone chooses to commit it.

what we need to get clear on is this:
women are not raped or murdered because of the clothes they wear.
women are not raped or murdered because of how much they choose to drink or where they choose to go out.
women are not raped or murdered because of the choices they made travelling home or where they live.
women are raped and murdered because another person chose to rape and/or murder. cont'd

text: #сказкипиздызлатовласки история эта началась давно, когда я также сидела за столом на завтраке одного из южных курортов. ко мне подошли редакторы журнала «не в коня корм» и предложили сделать специальный выпуск с большой фотографией на развороте с подробным описанием в остальной части журнала всего, что я ем в течение недели на курорте. они сказали, что этот номер наверняка станет глянцевым, так как читатели своими жирными пальцами заслюнявят все страницы, внимательно изучая мои пристрастия в еде. к сожалению, этот номер журнала стал финальным, потому что главные спонсоры издания - производители майонеза не увидели свой продукт в моём списке, а виноделы не заинтересовались, пусть и засаленным изрядно, изданием объемом в 4 страницы. дальше, как в сказке, голливудский продюсер искал на вилле, в которой раньше отдыхала я, бумажку. то ли селедку почистить, то ли ещё зачем она ему понадобилась. но наткнувшись на номер журнала, захваченный мною в путешествие, он уже не мог от него оторваться все 2 недели беспробудного отдыха. полетев домой, он связался со мной и предложил сняться в художественно-документальном фильме #жруинетолстею в главной роли по мотивам моего интервью. у нас было несколько рабочих встреч, обсуждений и вдруг я поняла, что продюсер смотрит на меня, как на еду, сальным взглядом. вы поняли, о ком я говорю. #metoo его предложение позавтракать вместе было столь заманчиво и многообещающе...получив отказ в категоричной форме (может потом, попозже?), он неприятно намекнул, что по его мнению я не смогу сняться в фильме, потому как у меня, видите ли, #жопарастёт и к моменту, когда он найдёт спонсора, я окончательно выйду в тираж. тогда я решительно отвергла саму возможность #всеилиничего съемки фильма по моему сценарию без меня в главной роли #пизжуинекраснею и тихо сижу получаю удовольствие от своего скромного завтрака. всем доброе утро!

stop_filter_tweet: история эта началась давно , когда я также сидела за столом на завтраке одного из южных курортов . ко мне подошли редакторы журнала « не в коня корм » и предложили сделать специальный выпуск с большой фотографией на развороте с подробным описанием в остальной части журнала всего , что я ем в течение недели на курорте . они сказали , что этот номер наверняка станет глянцевым , так как читатели своими жирными пальцами заслюнявят все страницы , внимательно изучая мои пристрастия в еде . к сожалению , этот номер журнала стал финальным , потому что главные спонсоры издания - производители майонеза не увидели свой продукт в моём списке , а виноделы не заинтересовались , пусть и засаленным изрядно , изданием объемом в 4 страницы . дальше , как в сказке , голливудский продюсер искал на вилле , в которой раньше отдыхала я , бумажку . то ли селедку почистить , то ли ещё зачем она ему понадобилась . но наткнувшись на номер журнала , захваченный мною в путешествие , он уже не мог от него оторваться все 2 недели беспробудного отдыха . полетев домой , он связался со мной и предложил сняться в художественно-документальном фильме в главной роли по мотивам моего интервью . у нас было несколько рабочих встреч , обсуждений и вдруг я поняла , что продюсер смотрит на меня , как на еду , сальным взглядом . вы поняли , о ком я говорю . его предложение позавтракать вместе было столь заманчиво и многообещающе ... получив отказ в категоричной форме ( может потом , попозже ? ) , он неприятно намекнул , что по его мнению я не смогу сняться в фильме , потому как у меня , видите ли , и к моменту , когда он найдёт спонсора , я окончательно выйду в тираж . тогда я решительно отвергла саму возможность съемки фильма по моему сценарию без меня в главной роли и тихо сижу получаю удовольствие от своего скромного завтрака . всем доброе утро !

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnn’s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analytica’s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from kogan’s app may not have been completely deleted. kogan’s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
yesterday, we were part of a great march #womensmarchla that takes place in the city of #losangeles.
we were here, this time with more reasons to be part of the feminist revolution. we were the voice of our women, our political prisoners, the strong women of #nicaragua. because to me, they represent me. they are sisters, cousins, nieces, daughters, but most importantly, they are #women and we as women must be together. together we are invincible, and remember very well!
there is no revolution without the participation of women!

500+ murdered by the government of nicaragua.
600+ political prisoners.
35,000+ nicaraguans exiled.
💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮💙🇳🇮

estuvimos aquí, esta vez con más motivos para ser parte de la revolución feminista. fuimos la voz de nuestras mujeres, nuestras presas políticas, las mujeres penconas de #nicaragua. porque a mi, ellas me representan. ellas son hermanas, primas, sobrinas, hijas, pero lo más importante, son #mujeres y nosotras como mujeres debemos estar juntas. juntas somos invendibles, ¡y recuerden muy bien! ¡no hay revolución sin la participación de las mujeres!

500+ asesinados por el gobierno de nicaragua.
600+ presos políticos.
35,000+ nicaragüenses exiliados.

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

here are those cool metal dolphins, veronica & i, and a lost googly eye, in #tallahassee at the neverending #womenswave yesterday. the weather was crazy windy but we had fun, and some great conversations about immigration law reform (i.e. the lack of such), open borders (my position), affordable healthcare for all (my position), and other interesting stuff. i was literally at the end of the line 🐢 lololol 🐢 during the march itself so didn't capture any crowd pictures. 🌺 pax amor.

i like many other black men have never allowed a non black to touch our hair, unless it was extreme cases. black men keep their money in the black community and pay black barbers consistent for hundreds of years.

the only times i have ever been to a non black barber was when i was traveling in europe. in uk a muslim indian cut my hair and in switzerland a filipino man cut my hair. in both cases i told them to bald it cuz i already knew they wasn't gonna give me that steve harvey line up.

black women religiously send asians and indians kids to college by purchasing their hair. then they come around and talk about how black men need to build. this is why i don't support that pro black love foolishness, these black women have the soul of white jesus embedded in their hearts.

text:
i am up early. full moon energy is intense. it’s magical. it’s powerful. and it’s illuminating truth.

this photo showed up just now- and i am not surprised.

these women have been through the fire. and they did it for their soul’s evolution... yes. maybe to find their voice for the first time- maybe because angels called them- but for sure- they did it for you... and for your children and grandchildren.

to the naysayers- let the moon illuminate the truth. please don’t fight with us. we’ve been through enough.  ultimately, the divine will unite us all again somehow. someday. hopefully it’s way before so many beautiful relationships in this world  have fallen apart forever.

in this short life... is it really worth choosing politics over love? for me- after all  i have endured these past two years- i still believe in love.

but- please don’t mess with these women- cuz i have also turned a bit badass 😉

#angel #badass #angel-badass (it’s the new way) #fiercelove

text:
(english below)
avec ce quatrième post, je vous présente la tenue que je souhaite coudre et broder entièrement pour clôturer ce premier projet, sur le thème de l’alphabet maya.
.
adolescente et très jeune adulte, je mettais une certaine coquetterie à utiliser du mieux que je le pouvais les vêtements bas de gamme que je possédais pour me mettre en valeur. 
il y a 4 ans, à la suite d’un reproche adressé par un ami, agacé du fait que je plaise à notre entourage, le regard des hommes a commencé à me sembler si pesant que j’ai voulu me rendre transparente. le vêtement est devenu un camouflage fonctionnel. je ne supportais plus que l’on me fasse des remarques non-sollicitées sur mon allure. comme tant d’autres femmes ont enfin osé l’exprimer depuis #metoo, je me sentais à la fois privée de la liberté de disposer de moi-même et condamnable pour mon image. en affadissant les tenues que je portais, j’espérais maîtriser le désir que je pouvais susciter pour ne plus me sentir responsable d’un regard ou d’un geste.
.
il m’a fallu traverser un long processus de déconstruction et cette formidable révolution féministe pour que commence à s’opérer le travail de guérison. il y a 6 mois, j’ai enfin ressenti au plus profond de mes cellules que je n’étais coupable de rien. chacun est responsable de son désir. 
aujourd’hui, je décide que je n’ai plus à me fondre dans le décor.
aujourd’hui, je me laisse prendre autant d’espace visuel que je le souhaite.
.
🇬🇧
how can we, as women, be as incredibly visible as we want, without also having to carry the weight of non-wanted men’s desire ?
.
#notresponsibleforyourdesire #asmuchvisibleasiwant #becomingmybestself #fabulouslydaring #mybodymyrules #promaker #feutrealcool

text:
she wears white but she’s not a virgin⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
her painted lips dont mean she’s yearning ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
a bare face doesn’t mean she had no time⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
and a full face of makeup isn’t a crime ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
a short skirt doesn’t mean that she’s asking⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
a smile could cover the pain she’s masking ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
her look can kill from across a dance floor⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
but all her flirting doesn’t mean she wants more
a kiss could mean she wants you to call⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
and then.. it could just mean.. nothing at all.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
equality, empowerment and respect for women all around the world 💪🏼 whatever choice you choose to make, make sure it’s your choice to choose. ⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

text:
je suis metteur en scène, et l'essence de mon métier est simple : créer les conditions nécessaires afin que deux groupes de personnes (acteurs et spectateurs) puissent partager une expérience intense, riche de sens, idéalement inoubliable. personnellement, je préfère m'appuyer sur un outil précieux : les histoires. 
mais qu'est-ce qu'une histoire ? et quelle responsabilité implique l'acte de raconter ? nous chercherons des réponses ensemble lundi prochain à 19h, en passant du bouclier d'achille au "non" de rosa parks, du mouvement #metoo au phénomène des séries télé.
rendez-vous lundi 21 à 19h à creatis, résidence d'entrepreneurs culturelspour présenter le nouveau programme why stories. les candidatures sont ouvertes pour le 3° parcours d'apprentissage qui se déroulera du 13 mars au 1er juin au labo de l'edition : contact@whystories.net
#whystories #whystoriesmatter #rosaparks #martinlutherking #civilrights #storytelling #labodeledition #creatis

text:
mai bhagh kaur (punjabi: ਮਾਈ ਭਾਗੋ) also known as mai bhago was a sikh woman who led sikh soldiers against the mughals in 1705.
she was an exceptionally skilled warrior on the battlefield and is revered as a saint in sikhism.
she was known for rallying the 40 sikhs (chali mukte) who abandoned guru gobind singh at the siege of anandpur sahib and bringing them back to fight. 
mai bhago stayed with guru gobind singh at talwandi sabo.
she may have adopted the garb of a nihang.
mai bhago became so spiritually absorbed that, according to the famous historical text suraj parkash, she would be absorbed in samadhi; her experiences were so profound that she forsook all her clothes and began living life nakedly as a sadhni.
the guru however ordered her to wear a small turban, kacchera, and wrap her self in a blanket as well as return to worldly ways and walk in maryada (code of conduct).
when the guru went to hazur sahib she became one of ten other bodyguards of the guru arming herself with a large lance (weighing about 102 pounds) and musket and did so in male attire.
mohan singh, jathedar of hazur sahib, in 1788 built a bunga (war tower) in the memory of mai bhag kaur.

text: фруктовый мармелад joyfield 🍏яркие вкусы на основе пектина, яблочного пюре и фруктозы дарят наслаждение и пользу. 👄оригинальные фигурки созданы фуд-скульпторами специально для joyfield. 🍑необычные вкусы и яркие цвета – классное лакомство для веселой компании. 💭невероятно нежная текстура – благодаря эксклюзивной рецептуре на основе яблочного пюре и пектина. ❌без сахара. в составе только фруктоза – натуральный источник энергии. 🎁стильная яркая упаковка – отличный вариант подарка. 🌱подходит вегетарианцам и веганам – в составе только продукты растительного происхождения.

i came across your video dear mr. player and after watching this i want to congratulate you,it was very well said.
but i have some questions for you
1.why you didn't say anything ,when sonam kapoor said " man can bring negativity in women's life.
2. when priyanka chopra said " i don't need a guy for anything except for children
3.you didn't say anything ,when we came to know that ,so many famous faces are involved in so called #metoo movement.
4. you didn't even say anything,when  a woman full of feminism said that all men are repist.
so tell me,can you give them a lesson on respect, gender sensitivity and sexism ?

may be you don't have the answer but i have.. u don't have that much guts to speak out against them because they all are from your field only.
there are so many(female celebrity) who gives this type of statements and everyone enjoy .
 now, this is specially for you- before judging anyone on the basis of a reality show, i would like to say i am a big fan of big boss
you know what i mean.
nothing against you.
thanks

 n last but not least...
aaj mein karke aaya hu ...sex
but i m not a rapist.

think before you speak.

text:
京都にある性被害の自助グループ「mint（ミント）」2月の活動予定のお知らせです❤︎
.
.
【self help group】
.
2019年2月16日（土）
13:00〜16:00
.
.
女性として生きる中で感じていることを気軽に話せる場所です。批判やアドバイスはせず、話すほうも聞くほうもお互いにありのままで受け止めます。主に性的なトラウマを抱える女性（女性の心をもつ方）を対象としていますが、性被害のご経験の有無に関わらず女性として生きてきた中で向き合いたいことやお話ししたいことがあるときに足を運んでみてくださいね。
.
（場所）
京都駅中央改札口より徒歩約12分
「しんらん交流館」1f会議室
.
（参加費）
500円  献金制
.
（お申し込み）
参加ご希望の方は下記①〜④の事項を添えてメールにてお申し込みください。折り返しご連絡いたします。
①メールの件名「ミント参加希望」
②お名前（ニックネーム可）
③メールアドレス
④ご希望の日程
selfhelpgroup.mint@gmail.com
.
会場へのアクセスなど自助グループについて詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「self help group」をご覧ください。
.
.
【online salon】
.
2019年2月26日（火） meeting
.
.
遠方の方や直接会うことに抵抗がある場合はオンラインサロンでもお話しすることができます。月に1回のミーティングのほか、お気に入りの音楽や写真をアップしたり自分の体験を綴ったり、ネット上に開設した当事者のためのサロンです。（サロンは性被害のご経験をもつ女性（女性の心をもつ方）専用としております。）
.
オンラインサロンについての詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「online salon」をご覧ください。
.
.
お話しできることを楽しみにしています(*^^*)
.
self help group「mint」
野間千華子
.
.
.

text:
la #donneemeraviglia di questa settimana è di origine calabrese, laureata in fisica, madre di un figlio. lucia votano, dal 2009 è la prima donna a dirigere i laboratori nazionali del gran sasso dell'istituto nazionale di fisica nucleare. con una carriera tutta all'interno dell'ifn intervallata dal soggiorno in germania e al cern, fa parte del peer review committee del coordinamento europeo per la fisica delle astro particelle, che nel settembre scorso ha delineato in un rapporto il futuro della ricerca astro particellare in europa. oggi coordina circa mille fisici provenienti da tutto il mondo che lavorano a una ventina di grandi progetti tra i quali quello che ha portato a dimostrare, insieme al cern di ginevra, l'esistenza del bosone di higgs.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
“tarana” 30 x 46. welcome to durham! artwork by durham art guild 2018 artist-in-residence @gemynii at @piecesofagem.⠀
⠀
from @triangletribune — “me too movement founder tarana burke will be the keynote speaker at duke university’s annual martin luther king jr. holiday celebration.⠀
⠀
burke, a civil rights activist who created the phrase in 2016, is part of a series of events honoring king this month.⠀
⠀
the theme of duke’s commemoration is ‘why words matter: from dissent to dialogue.’⠀
⠀
burke’s appearance is open to the public on jan. 20 at 3 p.m. in duke chapel.⠀
⠀
‘we rarely highlight dr. king’s activism aimed at pushing back on systems of power and privilege,’ said benjamin reese jr., vice president and chief diversity officer for the duke office for institutional equity. ‘ms. burke’s social justice work and her activism in highlighting sexual assault is a credit to dr. king’s legacy.’⠀
⠀
burke, who also is the senior director at girls for gender equity, initially wanted to bring to light sexual abuse and assault in this country. but the phrase caught fire and grew into the hashtag #metoo after the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations.⠀
⠀
burke and other activists nicknamed ‘the silence breakers’ by time magazine were honored as the 2017 time person of the year.⠀
⠀
those unable to attend the event can watch a live stream on duke’s youtube channel.”⠀
⠀

text:
in case anyone missed my liberating section of mortgage womens magazine “how to grow in perpetual change!” section where i named #3 of greatest change in 2018 the growth in the “me too” movement. 
take a read here.  raise your cups, your glasses or whatever you choose to celebrate but in a world where the words i have written publicly could have never been written let alone spoken two years ago, i say “hip hip hooray”! keep the ball rolling ladies!  i thought i would point this emerging “change” out.  in case anyone missed it.  let’s rock another year of growth and change!  keep your heels in the doors!  the only way to gain momentum is to take the lead when the moment strikes.  it’s here now, grab it. 
i am proud to have been featured in the mpa magazine as “most elite women” for 2018 “changing the face of gender equality for generations to come”! i plan to leave legacy work in this department. 
and for the record i love all you boys sincerely.  i’ve worked by greater percentages with men and with good men.  thank you for helping us have our moment. 
for the full article: https://lnkd.in/euywvuj
